modules.description: Controls how text blocks and tables are formatted, with options for line breaks, lists, and table rendering. Adjusts behavior for vertical and horizontal lists, preformatted text, and tree structures. Customizes indentation, quotation styles, and table framing based on specific output needs.

Provides functions to render structured data such as boxes, lists, arrays, and tables in text and HTML formats. Operates on custom data types representing nested containers and formatting options. Used to generate human-readable output for debugging or embedding structured information in web pages.

Manages text and table formatting in markdown output, offering control over line breaks, lists, and table structures. Supports vertical and horizontal list rendering, preformatted text, and tree layouts with customizable indentation and quotation styles. Processes table framing and alignment to meet specific output requirements. Enables precise control over markdown document structure and visual presentation.
